-- Diageo’s Kenyan Business Removes Chief Executive Officer Adetu
-- B y   S a r a h   M c G r e g o r
-- 2012-04-28T07:06:09Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-28/diageo-s-kenyan-business-removes-chief-executive-officer-adetu.html
Seni Adetu will step down as chief
executive officer of  East African Breweries Ltd. (EABL)  as of July 1
and move into the same position at  Guinness Nigeria Plc (GUINNESS) ,
according to EABL.  He will be replaced by Devlin Hainsworth, now managing
director of Guinness Nigeria, according to a statement published
in the Saturday Nation newspaper.  EABL, the Kenyan unit of distiller  Diageo Plc (DGE) , is Kenya’s
biggest company by market value. Guinness Nigeria is the
country’s second-biggest beer-maker by market value, is the
Nigerian unit of Diageo.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Sarah McGregor in Nairobi at 
 smcgregor5@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Paul Richardson at 
 pmrichardson@bloomberg.net  